This template walks you through customizing
a brochure. In this template, youll change
the following:
Replace and format text
Change background colors
Replace the photos with your own
Modify shapes
Save as an Illustrator file

Make a Brochure
in Illustrator CC
Last Step! STEP 6: Output
READ ALL OF THE INSTRUCTIONS BELOW FIRST.
Before printing or exporting your brochure from this
template, do the following to hide these instructions.
Choose Window > Artboards. Select the artboard
named Instructions and click the Delete Artboard
button ( ) at the bottom of the panel to remove it.
Choose Window > Layers to open the Layers panel.
Read ALL of the next steps before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to the
left of the Instructions layer and all other layers,
except for the layer named [Your Design Here].
Now output a copy in the format you need for your
use: To save as PDF (good for printing or for
exchanging when specifically asked for):
Choose File > Save As, then choose Adobe PDF.
STEP 5: Save as an Illustrator file
In Illustrato
r
, we begin by saving documents in the
Adobe Illustrator format (.ai). Think of the .ai file as
your original. You can then save or export another
copy in whatever format you need for a particular
use, as youll see in the next step. But first:
Choose File > Save. In the Save As dialog box,
name your file, choose a destination, and choose
the Adobe Illustrator (.ai) format.
Click Save. Click OK. Dont worry, your saved
document will not replace the template.
Read the ENTIRE next step before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to
the left of the Step 5 layer to hide the contents.
Click in the same column in the Layers panel to
the left of Step 6 to show that step.
STEP 4: Modify shapes
Select the black arrow ( ) in the Tools panel on
the left and click on the shape that the red arrow is
pointing to.
To resize the shape, click the bottom middle point
on the box around the shape and drag up or down.
If you want to move a shape, click in the color area
of the shape and drag.
To modify the shape, select the white arrow ( ) in
the Tools panel on the left. Click on any of the
anchor points around the shape. Click the same
anchor point again and drag to reshape the shape.
Read the ENTIRE next step before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to the
left of the Step 4 layer to hide the contents. Click
in the same column in the Layers panel to the left of
Step 5 to show that step.
STEP 3: Replace the photos with your own
Select the black arrow ( ) in the Tools panel on
the left. Click on the photo that the red arrow is
pointing to.
Click YOUR-PHOTO-HERE.jpg on the left side of the
Control panel above the document. Choose Relink.
Find a photo and click Place. The photo you place
should be at least large enough to fill the area.
To resize the image, you can Shift-drag a corner
handle. Release the mouse button and then the Shift
key. Click in the photo & drag to reposition it.
With the black arrow still selected, click directly on
any other photo in the brochure to select it. Follow
the previous steps to replace it.
Read the ENTIRE next step before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to the
left of the Step 3 layer to hide the contents. Click in
the same column in the Layers panel to the left of
Step 4 to show that step.
STEP 2: Change the background colors
Select the black arrow ( )
in the Tools panel on
the left.
Click to select the dark gray shape that the red
arrow is pointing to. With the shape selected, you
should see the following on the left end of the
Control panel above the document.
Click the Fill color ( ) in the Control panel
above the document and choose a color.
With the black arrow still selected, click directly
on any other color shape in the brochure to
select it. Follow the previous steps for changing
its color fill.
Read the ENTIRE next step before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to
the left of the Step 2 layer to hide the contents.
Click in the same column in the Layers panel to
the left of Step 3 to show that step.
STEP 1: Replace and format text
In this step, you will replace the placeholder text in
the brochure and also change text formatting.
Select the black arrow ( )
in the Tools panel
on the left. Click on the Explore the Wilderness
of Alaska text object that the red arrow is
pointing to.
Select the Type tool ( ) in the Tools panel on
the left.
Click directly in the Explore the Wilderness of
Alaska text that the red arrow is pointing to. With
the cursor in the text, drag over some or all of the
text to select it. Type your own text.
With the cursor in the text, again drag over some
or all of the text to select it. In the Control panel
above the document find the label Character.
Use the dropdown menus to the right of
Character to change the font, font style, or
font size of the selected text. (If you dont see
those menus, click the word Character to show
the menus.)
On the left side of the Control panel, change the
color fill of the selected text by clicking Fill color
and choosing a color.
With the Type tool selected, click directly in
any of the other text. With the cursor in the text,
drag over some or all of the text to select it.
Follow the previous steps for changing the text
and its formatting.
Read the ENTIRE next step before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to
the left of the Step 1 layer to hide the contents.
Click in the same column in the Layers panel to
the left of Step 2 to show that step.
The steps to complete will appear in this area. To
show the different steps, you will show and hide
layers in the Layers panel.
To get started, open the Layers panel by
choosing Window > Layers.
In the Layers panel, click once on the layer name
[Your Design Here] to select that layer. Leave
that layer selected throughout.
Read the ENTIRE next step before doing anything.
In the Layers panel, click the eye icon ( ) to
the left of the Start layer to hide the contents.
THEN, click in the same column in the Layers
panel to the left of Step 1 to show that step.
